cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 350 degrees.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce (except kale). Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%oz}. Quarter @Lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Bell Pepper{1} into strips.

Toss kale on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide kale between 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.) Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{13-15%minutes}.

> Watch kale carefully to ensure it doesn't burn.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tbsp}, @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the @Garlic Powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and a squeeze of lemon juice. If needed, add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @Yellow Onion{1}(thinly sliced) and @Bell Pepper{1}(thinly sliced), and a pinch of salt and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred and tender, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Honey{2%tsp}, remaining @Garlic Powder{1/2%tsp}, and 1 tsp water (2 tsp for 4 servings) until combined. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wash out pan.

While veggies cook, slice @Grilling Cheese{8%oz} lengthwise into six pieces (12 pieces for 4 servings). In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the @Curry Powder{1/2%tbsp} and @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} (for 4, use all the curry powder and 4 TBSP olive oil). Add grilling cheese and toss to coat.

Heat pan used for the veggies over medium heat. Add grilling cheese in a single layer; cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side (for 4, you may need to work in batches).

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Divide rice, veggies, and roasted kale between bowls. Top with grilling cheese and drizzle with as much sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.